Net judgment: Elton John’s live transfer better preserves the punch, separation and centered lead presence I prioritize even if it isn’t a glossy pop single compilation. The Crystalline studio mastering is sonically excellent but leans toward integrated harmonies and medley sequencing that conflict with my dislike for atmosphere‑first mixes that can obscure hooky, mid‑forward vocals.

